# local-model.Modelfile
# Builds a custom Ollama model tag from Qwen3.5-9B, replacing the earlier
# Qwen2.5-Coder 7B pick. Qwen3.5-9B has much longer native context (262K vs
# 32K), stronger tool-calling benchmarks, and is the right generation for
# an 8GB-class card, Qwen3.6 needs 16GB+ even at its smallest dense size.
#
# TEXT ONLY / NO VISION: Qwen3.5 is natively multimodal, but in GGUF form
# vision only loads if you separately download the mmproj-f16.gguf file.
# Just don't download it. There is no separate "text-only quant" to pick,
# skipping the mmproj file is the entire difference.
#
# Quant: UD-Q5_K_XL (Unsloth Dynamic, layer-aware quantization), 6.74 GB.
# Best quality that still leaves headroom for KV cache on a 7.7 GB card.
# Falls back to plain Q5_K_M (6.58 GB) if you hit loading issues with the
# UD variant.
#
# Download (check the exact filename on the repo's file listing first,
# Unsloth's naming can vary slightly by upload). huggingface-cli is
# deprecated, use the current hf CLI:
#   pip install -U huggingface_hub --break-system-packages
#   hf download hf://unsloth/Qwen3.5-9B-GGUF/Qwen3.5-9B-UD-Q5_K_XL.gguf --local-dir ./
#
# Then build the tag, pointing FROM at the downloaded file, not a model
# name (this is a local GGUF import, not an ollama pull):
#   ollama create local-qwen35-coder-cc -f ./local-model.Modelfile

FROM ./Qwen3.5-9B-UD-Q5_K_XL.gguf

# Context window: 20K tokens, same reasoning as before, balance of
# capability vs VRAM headroom on a 7.7 GB card.
PARAMETER num_ctx 20480

# Keep the model resident after use so back-to-back requests don't pay a
# reload penalty. Lower this if you need the VRAM back between sessions.
PARAMETER num_keep 24
